body.story: It's a beautiful Tuesday in Queens. I'm swinging home, thinking about Aunt May's wheatcakes, when BAM! A giant energy dome appears over Times Square! People scream, cars crash, and the sky turns purple. Definitely not on the tourist brochures.

dialogues.line: Okay, dome-y, what's your deal? Is this a hostile takeover or just bad weather?
Spider-Man! Help! It's draining all the color from everything!

choices.label: Swing directly into the energy dome!

panel_layout.description: Spider-Man is swinging towards Times Square, a thought bubble showing Aunt May's wheatcakes above his head. Bright, sunny day in Queens.
Wide shot of Times Square. A massive, purple energy dome has appeared, casting a sickly light. Cars are crashed, people are screaming and running.
Close-up on a citizen, face contorted in fear, pointing at the energy dome. Spider-Man is landing nearby, a concerned expression on his face.

illustration.art_direction: Dynamic angles and perspective to emphasize Spider-Man's movement and the chaos. Panel 1 uses a classic comic book feel with clean lines and bright colors. Panel 2 uses a wide, almost panoramic view to showcase the scale of the dome. Panel 3 is a close-up to connect the reader with the immediate danger and fear.
illustration.color_palette: Panel 1: bright blues, reds, yellows. Panel 2: sickly purple, muted grays, desaturated colors. Panel 3: emphasizes the fading color.
illustration.lighting: Panel 1: Sunny, natural lighting. Panel 2: Ominous purple glow emanating from the dome, washing out colors. Panel 3: Dim, fading light with stark shadows.
